7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Amazon CodeWhisperer (Q Developer) and MarsCode share a solid foundation of core features including Autocomplete, Code Generation, Debugging, Multi Language. Where Amazon CodeWhisperer (Q Developer) pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Code Review and Refactoring and Ide Integration and Documentation, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Amazon CodeWhisperer (Q Developer) holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while MarsCode scores 5/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, MarsCode comes in at a lower starting price of $0, while Amazon CodeWhisperer (Q Developer) begins at $19/mo. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Amazon CodeWhisperer (Q Developer)'s free tier and MarsCode's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
